# Next.js App Router Conventions

## File & Folder Naming

- Route segments use **kebab-case** directories: `app/(dashboard)/user-management/page.tsx`
- Route groups use parentheses for layout isolation: `(auth)`, `(dashboard)`
- Colocation: keep `loading.tsx`, `error.tsx`, and `not-found.tsx` next to each `page.tsx`

## Server vs Client Components

```
// ✅ Default to Server Components — no 'use client' unless needed
// Add 'use client' only when you need: useState, useEffect, event handlers, browser APIs
```

- Never fetch data inside a Client Component — lift fetches to the nearest Server Component and pass data as props.
- Data fetching functions live in `src/lib/api/` and are **never duplicated**.

## No Duplication Policy

- Shared fetch wrappers live in `src/lib/api/<resource>.ts` — one file per domain entity.
- Shared types live in `src/types/<resource>.ts` — imported everywhere, never re-declared.
- Any repeated UI pattern (≥ 2 occurrences) must be extracted to the appropriate atomic level.

## State Management

- Server state → use React Server Components + `fetch` (with Next.js cache).
- Client/UI state → `useState` or `useReducer` inside hooks.
- Global client state → Zustand store in `src/store/<name>.store.ts`.
